## Problem
In `src/main.ts:109-117`, the `ensureFolderExists()` method checks if something exists at the path, but doesn't verify it's actually a folder:

```typescript
private async ensureFolderExists(folderPath: string): Promise<void> {
  const folder = this.app.vault.getAbstractFileByPath(folderPath);
  if (!folder) {
    await this.app.vault.createFolder(folderPath);
  }
}
```

## Impact
If a user has a FILE named 'Archive' instead of a folder, this method returns without error. Then `vault.rename()` fails with a confusing error when trying to move the project into it.

## Fix
Add an `instanceof TFolder` check and throw a clear error:

```typescript
if (!folder) {
  await this.app.vault.createFolder(folderPath);
} else if (!(folder instanceof TFolder)) {
  throw new Error(`"${folderPath}" exists but is not a folder`);
}
```

