## Problem
In `src/utils.ts:110-112`, the error branch when too many collisions occur is untested:

```typescript
if (counter > MAX_COLLISION_ATTEMPTS) {
  throw new Error('Too many archive collisions - please clean up your archive folder');
}
```

## Fix
Add test in `tests/utils.test.ts` that creates a Set which always returns `has() === true`:

```typescript
it('throws error when MAX_COLLISION_ATTEMPTS exceeded', () => {
  // Create a Set-like object that always reports collision
  const alwaysCollides = {
    has: () => true,
  } as Set<string>;

  expect(() => 
    generateArchiveDestination('Archive', 'Project', alwaysCollides)
  ).toThrow('Too many archive collisions');
});
```

Or use a real Set with 1001+ entries (slower but more realistic).

## Files
- tests/utils.test.ts (add new test in generateArchiveDestination describe block)

## Problem
In `tests/utils.test.ts:133-137`, the `generateArchiveDestination` test suite uses fake timers but never restores them:

```typescript
describe('generateArchiveDestination', () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    vi.useFakeTimers();
    vi.setSystemTime(new Date('2024-03-15T12:00:00Z'));
  });
  // Missing: afterEach(() => vi.useRealTimers());
```

## Impact
Fake timers leak into subsequent test files if test order changes or new test files are added. This can cause flaky tests that are hard to debug.

## Fix
Add afterEach cleanup:

```typescript
afterEach(() => {
  vi.useRealTimers();
});
```

Or use `vi.restoreAllMocks()` if other mocks are added later.

