## Problem
In `src/main.ts:40`, the onClick handler returns a Promise but isn't marked async:

```typescript
.onClick(() => this.archiveFolder(file));
```

This returns a Promise that Obsidian ignores. It works, but the intent is unclear.

## Suggested Fix
Either make it explicitly async (if we want to await):
```typescript
.onClick(async () => {
  await this.archiveFolder(file);
});
```

Or use void to indicate fire-and-forget:
```typescript
.onClick(() => {
  void this.archiveFolder(file);
});
```

The first option is preferred as it matches the pattern used elsewhere in the codebase.

