## Problem
In `src/main.ts:121-126`, when confirmation modal is enabled, the Promise only resolves if user clicks 'Archive':

```typescript
if (this.settings.confirmBeforeArchive) {
  return new Promise<void>((resolve) => {
    new ArchiveConfirmModal(this.app, folderName, destPath, async () => {
      await this.performArchive(folder, destPath, folderName, archivePath);
      resolve();
    }).open();
  });
}
```

If user:
- Presses Escape
- Clicks outside modal
- Clicks Cancel button

The Promise never resolves. The `archiveFolder` function hangs indefinitely (doesn't block UI since async, but semantically wrong).

## Fix
Add onCancel callback or resolve in onClose:

**Option A: Add onCancel parameter**
```typescript
class ArchiveConfirmModal extends Modal {
  private onCancel: () => void;

  constructor(app: App, folderName: string, destPath: string, onConfirm: () => void, onCancel: () => void) {
    // ...
    this.onCancel = onCancel;
  }

  onClose() {
    this.onCancel(); // Always call on close
    this.contentEl.empty();
  }
}
```

**Option B: Track if confirmed**
```typescript
private confirmed = false;

// In confirm handler:
this.confirmed = true;
this.onConfirm();
this.close();

// In onClose:
if (!this.confirmed) {
  // User cancelled
}
```

